89
00:05:01.980 --> 00:05:04.980
I did. It's an amazing fact, but apparently true.

90
00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:12.980
Yes, indeed. Okay, so let's recap the vocabulary we've learned in this episode, starting with the phrase 100%.

91
00:05:12.980 --> 00:05:20.980
Which can be used to emphasise that you completely agree with something or that you consider something to be completely right or wrong.

92
00:05:20.980 --> 00:05:27.980
If you describe a movement as jerky, you mean it move suddenly and stops and starts rather than flowing smoothly.

93
00:05:27.980 --> 00:05:31.980
The adjective intentional means planned and purposeful.

94
00:05:31.980 --> 00:05:38.980
The phrase to the naked eye means in a way that can be seen without special instruments or to someone without special knowledge.

95
00:05:38.980 --> 00:05:45.980
The idiom love at first sight describes the experience of starting to love someone as soon as you see them for the first time.

96
00:05:45.980 --> 00:05:55.980
And finally, an unhelpful cliché is an overused phrase or comment, a cliché, which has the effect of creating unhelpful or unrealistic attitudes.

97
